gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Jazz 127, Wizards 115
gameRecap.excerpt: Utah defeats Washington, 127-115. For Utah, Jordan Clarkson led the way with a season-high 38 points, 10 rebounds, and seven assists while aided by Collin Sexton (29 points, seven assists) and John Collins (17 points, 15 rebounds, career-high six blocks) in the victory. Jordan Poole tallied 32 points (six 3PM) and two steals with Kyle Kuzma recording 23 points, five rebounds, and eight assists for Washington in the losing effort. Utah improves to 28-34 on the season, while Washington moves to 9-52 with the loss.
